    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="26"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d26fn1">Sent by the United States Military Attaché, London,
                        via Army channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Excerpts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-27">27 November
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>
                    Personal and Top Secret Number 834.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>2. Your 658. I agree with your conclusion that U. J. will not travel beyond the
                    Black Sea but I am sure the ports there will be unfit for us until the winter
                    has passed.<note n="2" xml:id="d26fn2">The paragraph here omitted is printed <hi
                            rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_287">pp. 287</ref>–<ref
                            target="#pg_288">288</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Prime</hi>
                        <note n="3" xml:id="d26fn3">A handwritten notation in the margin by Leahy
                            reads: “No reply necessary.”</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
